About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
----------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr Tarak Mehta. This story evolves around happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. The show predominantly revolves around 'Jethalaal' (Dilip Joshi), an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta' (Sailesh Lodha), is his neighbour. 'Jethalaal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Raj Anankat). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalaal' to reform 'Tapu' or be prepared to leave the premises.

About The Show:
----------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a comedy show inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada Family which consists of uneducated businessmen Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalalâ€™s Wife Daya & their naughty Son Tipendra Gada living in 'Gokuldham Co-operative Society' and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. In case of a problem and emergency, Jethalal Gada often rushes to Taarak Mehta to seek his help and guidance as he finds a philosopher in him. The housing society residents help each other find solutions when facing common, real-life challenges and getting involved in sticky situations.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
----------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr Tarak Mehta. This story evolves around happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. The show predominantly revolves around 'Jethalaal' (Dilip Joshi), an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta' (Sailesh Lodha), is his neighbour. 'Jethalaal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Raj Anankat). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalaal' to reform 'Tapu' or be prepared to leave the premises.

Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah Playlist: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLfyXOEyr93G1DSZ-26hoFNNWQ9Jnu9kZu

Todayâ€™s recipe is Diwali faral shankarpali using 1 kilo maida. It turns out nice, crispy and flaky. Diwali faral is incomplete without shankarpali. We already have seen different recipes if shankarpali. This is full proof recipe the proportion used is just perfect. It is a very easy and simple recipe. You can make it within no time. Besides, I am sharing few tips to make perfect shankarpali. This is a popular Marathi recipe. Also it can be a good tea time snack. You can try this recipe at home and drop a comment for me. Click here to subscribe to SAB: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC6-F5tO8uklgE9Zy8IvbdFw?sub_confirmation=1

Episode 3921: Chand Par Padosi
--------------------------------------------------------
Jetha eventually sees Mr. Chand and talks about the lunar plot and how to buy it without any complications. Mr. Chand explains to Jetha the high demand in society for a lunar plot. He claims that high-profile political figures and movie actors want to acquire property on the Moon. Jetha is taken in by his words and promptly books three plots. Bagha and Nattu Kaka are overjoyed by the news, but how will Champaklal react? Watch the episode to find out what happens when Jetha tells his father about his newly purchased property.

About the show: 
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a SAB Comedy Show inspired by the famous humorous column, Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah written by the eminent Gujarati writer, Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada family which consists of businessman, Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal's wife, Daya & their naughty son, Tipendra Gada living in Gokuldham Co-operative Society, and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. This hilarious show will surely tickle your funny bone.

Ingredients:
Bhajani
â€¢ 2 1/2 cup / 500 gm Rice
â€¢ 1 cup / 200 gm Chana dal
â€¢ 1/2 cup / 100 gm Moong dal
â€¢ 1/2 cup / 100 gm Urad dal
â€¢ 1/2 cup / 100 gm Poha
â€¢ 20 gm Coriander seeds
â€¢ 20 gm Cumin seeds
Chakali
â€¢ 3 cups Water
â€¢ 1/4 cup Oil
â€¢ 1 tsp Oil
â€¢ 1 tsp Red chili powder
â€¢ Salt to taste
â€¢ 1 tbsp Coriander powder
â€¢ 1 kilo Chakali bhajani
â€¢ 1 tsp Ajwain / Carom seeds
â€¢ 1 tsp white Sesame seeds
â€¢ Oil for frying

Method:
â€¢ Wipe the rice really good with a clean wet cotton cloth. 
â€¢ Wipe chana dal really good with clean wet cotton cloth. 
â€¢ Wipe moong dal really good with a clean wet cotton cloth. 
â€¢ Wipe urad dal really good with a clean wet cotton cloth. 
â€¢ You can wash and dry all these ingredients if you want. 
â€¢ Heat up a pan on medium heat and roast rice really good. 
â€¢ The rice should be roasted well but the color should not change. 
â€¢ When the rice is roasted well take it out into a dish. 
â€¢ In the same pan roast chana dal really good until it begins to get reddish color and take it out into 
  a dish. 
â€¢ In the same pan roast moong dal well until it gets reddish color and take it out into a dish. 
â€¢ In the same pan roast urad dal really good until it gets light golden color and take it out into a 
  dish. 
â€¢ Roast poha really good and transfer them into the dish. 
â€¢ In the same pan roast coriander seeds and cumin seeds together on low heat until nice aroma 
  begins to release from it and transfer it into the dish. 
â€¢ Mix everything well together and let it cool down. 
â€¢ Grind it from the mill. Make sure that it is ground after rice or jawar is ground and not after wheat. 
â€¢ Blend it into flour in mixer and sieve it through flour strainer. 
â€¢ Blend the leftover coarse flour in the strain again in blender and sieve it. Bhajani for chakali is 
  ready.
Chakali
â€¢ Heat up water in a pan and add oil. 
â€¢ Mix well and add red chili powder, salt, coriander powder. 
â€¢ Mix well and when the mixture boils really good, reduce the heat to low. 
â€¢ Add the bhajani flour and turn off the gas. 
â€¢ Add carom seeds, sesame seeds and mix everything well together quickly. 
â€¢ Transfer the ukad into a dish and knead dough. If needed use very little hot water. 
â€¢ Knead the ukad really good when it is still hot. The consistency of the dough should be stiff. 
â€¢ Take small portion from the dough and knead it really good again. 
â€¢ Make a smooth and even roll and transfer it into chakali machine. 
â€¢ Press the dough well and roll out chakali from it on a butter paper. 
â€¢ Seal both the ends of the chakali really good. 
â€¢You can use plastic sheet or dish in place of butter paper. 
â€¢ Heat up oil in a pan on medium to high heat for about 6-7 minutes and drop a small chakali in it. 
â€¢ If it is fried well, then the oil is hot enough. 
â€¢ Drop chakali into hot oil and fry well. 
â€¢ When the chakali begins to settle at the bottom, flip it over and fry well from other side too. 
â€¢ When chakali begins to settle at the bottom of the pan, it means it is fried well from both sides. 
â€¢ Take the chakali out, drain excess oil and transfer it into a dish. Chakali is ready.

Discover how they've defied societal norms to find love and happiness, and learn about their inspiring journey as successful content creators. Don't miss this fascinating episode that celebrates love in all its forms.

Mannat Murad Episode 12 - [Eng Sub] - Iqra Aziz - Talha Chahour - Digitally Presented by PEL - 6th November 2023 - HAR PAL GEO

Mannat Murad Digitally Presented by PEL

Mannat is a beautiful young girl who hails from a progressive family that values love, care, and mutual respect. Raised in an environment where everyone's choices are respected, Mannat enjoys the freedom to make her own decisions. Following the untimely demise of her parents, she finds support from her elder brother, Nafees, who showers her with affection.

On the other hand, Murad belongs to a conservative family where his mother, the matriarch, wields significant influence over his life choices. As the only son, Murad is burdened with the responsibility of fulfilling his family's expectations. Soft-spoken and romantic by nature, Murad finds himself unable to defy his mother's authority, especially after the passing of his father.

Despite their starkly contrasting backgrounds, Mannat and Murad's hearts find solace in each other's presence, and they fall deeply in love. However, their families' interference creates misunderstandings between Mannat and Murad, testing the strength of their bond.

Will their families agree to their union? Will Mannat's family, with their open-mindedness, find common ground with Murad's conservative household? Can Mannat and Murad's love for each other withstand the motives of their families, who seek to create further misunderstandings between them?

Written by: Nadia Akhtar
Directed by: Syed Wajahat Hussain
Produced by: Abdullah Kadwani & Asad Qureshi
Production House: 7th Sky Entertainment

snippet.description:
Click here to subscribe to SAB: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC6-F5tO8uklgE9Zy8IvbdFw?sub_confirmation=1

Episode 3920: Moon Residential Program
--------------------------------------------------------
Bawri enters Gada Shop and discusses the popular video about acquiring a lunar plot. Bagha discusses to Jetha the vitality of emerging technology. Bagha discusses cryptocurrency and bitcoins. Jetha is enthusiastic about understanding the significance of NFT and the metaverse. All of these new advances in technology urge Jetha to contact the MRP (Moon Residential Programme) management and reserve a site. Jetha finally appears at the MRP's local Mumbai office to buy Babita's land. Watch the episode to find out how Jetha closes the deal with Mr. Chand, the manager.

Star Cast â€“  Dilip Joshi, Disha Vakani, Amit Bhatt, Nitish Bhaluni

About the show: 
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a SAB Comedy Show inspired by the famous humorous column, Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah written by the eminent Gujarati writer, Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada family which consists of businessman, Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal's wife, Daya & their naughty son, Tipendra Gada living in Gokuldham Co-operative Society, and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. This hilarious show will surely tickle your funny bone.

This story revolves around Mehreen and her daughter Areej, who was born after years of prayers. Prior to her birth, Mehreen and her husband had been caring for Salman, Areej's cousin. However, a tragedy struck, separating Areej from her family. Afterwards, Mehreen decided to raise Salman as her own son.
Years later, Salman crosses paths with Urooj, a beautiful and fearless girl, the daughter of school teacher Shoaib and his wife Naseem. snippet.title: Baylagaam Mega Ep 28 - [Eng Sub] - Ali Abbas - Laiba Khan - Haroon Shahid - Tuba Anwar - 5th Nov 23
snippet.description:
Thanks for watching Har Pal Geo. Please click here https://bit.ly/3rCBCYN to Subscribe and hit the bell icon to enjoy Top Pakistani Dramas and satisfy all your entertainment needs. Do you know Har Pal Geo is now available in the US? Share the News. Spread the word.

Baylagaam Mega Episode 28 - [Eng Sub] - Ali Abbas - Laiba Khan - Haroon Shahid - Tuba Anwar - 5th November 2023 - HAR PAL GEO

The story centers around Ramsha, a young girl and the only child of her loving parents, Sajid and Mehnaz. Raised with affection and no restrictions, Ramsha enjoys unlimited internet access, which leads to her spending an excessive time on social media, quickly becoming her hobby.
As her fascination with social media intensifies, Ramsha's hobby evolves into an all-consuming passion for fame, prompting her to take extreme measures. During her relentless pursuit of stardom, she crosses paths with Afnan, the son of the influential businessman Qasim Ali. While Afnan, who holds affection for his paternal cousin Aleezay, views Ramsha as a source of amusement, she misinterprets their friendship as love.
Disheartened by her failed search for love, Ramsha turns towards fame. Ramsha's unwavering quest for popularity propels her onto a challenging path, causing turmoil within her family. As her popularity soars, she becomes increasingly distant from her loved ones, leading her life down a tumultuous road, where she discovers the other side of fame many people are unaware of. Along this journey, she encounters Afnan once more, but circumstances have taken a different turn.
Will Ramsha achieve the fame she so desperately desires? Will her pursuit bring dire consequences? Can she find contentment in fame instead of love? And will Ramsha's parents have to bear the consequences of her passion?

Directed By: Zahid Mehmood
